sudo apt-get install mono-complete



FONTE:
https://www.dedoimedo.com/computers/wine-dotnet-mono.html



Wine can use a Windows build of Mono to run . NET applications.


_____________________________________________
# ALL IN ALL
sudo apt install wine mono-complete wine32


sudo apt install wine --no-install-recommends

does not install wine32, while

sudo apt install wine --install-recommends
sudo apt install wine64 --install-recommends

does, if i386 architecture is added.

OU

sudo apt install -t bullseye-backports wine64 --install-recommends

sudo apt install -t bullseye-backports wine --install-recommends

_____________________________________________
# WINE32 ( BACKPORTS )
sudo apt install -t bullseye-backports wine32
